## Your Task

- **ID**: BUG-260709-21pjyu
- **Title**: BUG-260709-21pjyu: appmetrica-reports-after-activation-failure
- **Parent**: STORY-260707-1zg543
### Description

Fix ReluxAnalytics AppMetrica aggregator activation handling. The aggregator stores the boolean result of AppMetrica activation, but identify and track currently continue to set identity/report events even if activation returned false. This can send calls through an inactive or misconfigured AppMetrica client and hides activation failure semantics from tests.
### Scope

ReluxAnalytics AppMetrica integration and its tests only. Do not change public analytics event models unless required for the fix. Do not commit, push, tag, or rewrite history in this worker run.
### Acceptance Criteria

If AppMetrica activation fails, identify and track do not call AppMetrica reportEvent, setUserProfileID, or sendEventsBuffer for that failed activation state. Activation remains idempotent and successful activation behavior is unchanged. Tests cover activation failure and successful activation paths. The package test suite or the targeted ReluxAnalytics tests pass locally.

## Instructions

The following instructions have been attached to this task:

### BUG-260709-21pjyu_review-finding.md
> Self-review finding and implementation hints

Review finding: integrations/appmetrica/Sources/ReluxAnalyticsAppMetrica/Analytics+AppMetricaService.swift has AppMetricaAggregator.start set activated = await client.activate(apiKey:), but track calls await start() and then report(...) regardless of whether activated is true. identify also calls start(), then setUserProfileID and report analytics_identified. Fix should prevent AppMetrica reporting/identity/flush calls after failed activation while preserving successful activation behavior and idempotence. Add focused tests around a fake AppMetrica client activation=false. Do not commit, push, tag, or rewrite history; leave changes ready for coordinator review.




