## Querying & Mutating the Board

Three primary access modes following the [agent-facing-api](https://github.com/relux-works/skill-agent-facing-api) pattern — all through one CLI binary:

- **`q` (query DSL)** — structured reads: `task-board q --format compact 'list(type=task, status=development) { overview }'`
- **`grep` (full-text search)** — scoped text search: `task-board grep "AudioRecorder"` (local only)
- **`m` (mutation DSL)** — structured writes: `task-board m 'set_status(TASK-260218-abc, status=done)'`

Plus a CLI plan facade for pretty-print / render / save: `task-board plan ...`, and local-only utilities such as `validate` (structure check).

Field presets: `minimal` (id, status), `default` (id, name, status), `overview` (+ assignee, parent), `full` (all 18 fields), `progress` (status, checklist, notes, blocked), `planning` (status, blocks, parent).

When mentioning board elements in human-facing responses, always include both the concrete ID and the human-readable title/name. This applies to epics, stories, tasks, and bugs. ID-only references are not enough for people scanning the chat because they should not have to resolve identifiers manually.

For DSL operations, mutations reference, field projection, and decision table — see [`references/querying.md`](references/querying.md).

