## Tips

- **Detail stories before planning** — create tasks for all stories before phase planning, so the plan shows real scope
- **AC must be verifiable** — "works" is bad, "test passes" is good
- **Update progress immediately** — don't defer
- **Use checklist** for tracking subtasks within a task
- **Bugs live in stories** — always attach to a relevant story
- **Sub-agents write tests** — every sub-agent is responsible for tests in its scope
- **Supervisor coordinates reviews** — coordinator must spawn/review-route child reviewer work before marking done
- **Visualize at milestones** — render graphs before, during, and after execution with `task-board plan --render`
- **Verify agents early** — run `task-board q 'agents()'` within 2 minutes of launch; if status not updated, stop and restart with better prompt
- **Concrete IDs only** — never use placeholders like `TASK-XXX` in prompts; always use real IDs like `TASK-260203-ae3fcd`
- **Human-facing references need ID + title/name** — when mentioning an epic, story, task, or bug in chat, include both so people can understand the reference without looking up the ID
- **No work without a task** — every code change must be tracked on the board. If a task doesn't exist, create one first. Don't start coding then retroactively create tasks
- **Parent is orchestrator, not worker** — the parent agent plans, creates/refines board items, spawns children, watches `RUN-...` handles, sends directives, and decides next routing. It must not do implementation, research, testing, docs, or review inline when a board task can be delegated.
- **Do not force-fit broken assumptions** — if the clean path is blocked by a platform/API/product/architecture constraint, stop. Document the evidence and options, then ask the human or set `blocked`; do not spend more time building a tower of stubs, flags, priority rules, and tests around an invalid model.
- **All task work through tracked background spawn** — every task on the board (research, analysis, implementation, testing, docs, and review) MUST be executed via `task-board spawn ... --background` which launches **separate CLI processes** (`claude -p` / `codex exec`), not internal sub-agents. `--background` is an explicit execution flag and must be present. Never use the Task tool or manual shell background agents for board work.
- **Reviews are child work too** — when work reaches `to-review`, spawn `task-board spawn TASK-... --role reviewer --background`. The parent orchestrator reads the review outcome and routes the item to `done` or back to `to-dev`; it does not perform the review inline.
- **`to-review` is not done** — producers must report `to-review` as "ready for review" or "handed off to review". Coordinators must not tell the human "done"/"complete"/"finished"/"final"/"готово" until a reviewer has accepted the work and the board item is actually `done`.
- **Coordinators track `RUN-...`, not shell jobs** — after spawning, hold onto the returned run id and drive orchestration with `task-board spawn status/events/watch/wait`. Do not rely on `&`, `nohup`, or runtime background wrappers to track completion
- **Drive unblocked tasks to terminal handoff** — if no objective blocker remains, the spawned worker must keep going until it has checked the relevant checklist items, attached outcome evidence, and moved the task to its role `end_status` (`to-review` for producers, `done` for reviewers). Do not leave tasks stalled in `analysis`, `development`, `testing`, or `reviewing`; use `blocked` only for real external blockers and document the evidence.
- **Dependent children are sequenced** — if child B consumes or reviews child A's output, the parent must `spawn wait` child A, inspect status/outcome resources, and only then spawn child B. Parallel fan-out is only for independent tasks.
- **`--role` is REQUIRED on spawn** — never spawn without a role. Pick the right role for the task: `researcher` for analysis, `developer` for code, `tester` for tests, `solution-architect` for decomposition, `doc-writer` for docs, `reviewer` for reviews. The role drives the agent's identity, skills, lifecycle (status transitions), and definition of done
- **`project_config()` first** — before spawn or spawn-contract review, run `task-board q 'project_config()'` so you know whether the current cwd is local or remote and which shared `spawn` settings are in effect
- **Resource CRUD is explicit** — `add_resource` / `resource add` create a new named resource and must not silently overwrite; use `update_resource` / `resource update` to replace an existing resource; use `delete_resource` / `resource delete` to remove one
- **Inline text resources via DSL** — use `task-board m 'add_resource(...)'` for create and `task-board m 'update_resource(...)'` for replacement when the payload is short text that already fits naturally in DSL
- **File and URL attachments via CLI** — use `task-board resource add TASK-... ./file.png --type precondition`, `task-board resource update TASK-... ./file.png`, and `task-board resource delete TASK-... NAME`
- **Artifact names must include the task ID** — when attaching outcome artifacts or task-specific instructions, include the owning task ID in the resource name, e.g. `TASK-260218-abc123_results.md`
- **Chat attachments need the bridge, not the board** — if the file exists only as a chat attachment and has no local path, install [`alexis-agents-infra`](https://github.com/relux-works/alexis-agents-infra), run `agents-attachments materialize`, then pass the resolved path into `task-board resource add`
- **Precondition resources = agent instructions** — when spawning via `task-board spawn`, precondition resources are auto-injected into the agent prompt via the template
- **Ignore stale `.temp` worktrees during audits** — when reviewing help/docs/source for spawn drift, search canonical source paths with `.temp/**` excluded; historical `.temp/*/skill-project-management-worktree/` copies can contain obsolete spawn files
- **Research goes to `.research/` AND resources** — all research results persist in `.research/{YYMMDD}_{topic}.md` (project-level) AND as outcome resources on the task. See [`references/research-workflow.md`](references/research-workflow.md)
- **Plans go to `.planning/`** — after phase planning, persist them with `task-board plan --save` to `.planning/{YYMMDD}_{HHmmss}_{topic}.md` for session recovery. See [`references/planning-workflow.md`](references/planning-workflow.md)
- **Legacy token in config** — if you see `remote.token` in `task-board.config.json`, suggest running `scripts/migrate-credentials.sh --user USER_ID` to move it to the credentials store

